FBIS4-63285 "drsov098_f_94001" FBIS-SOV-94-098 Daily Report 19 May 1994 National Affairs Crimean President Says Situation Calm Crimean President Says Situation Calm LD1905192394 Moscow Ostankino Television First Channel Network in Russian 1700 GMT 19 May 94 LD1905192394 Moscow Ostankino Television First Channel Network Russian BFN [From the "Novosti" newscast] [Text] Thirty minutes ago we telephoned Crimean President Yuriy Meshkov and asked him to comment on the situation. [Begin Meshkov recording] The situation in Crimea is calm. The attempts to influence our peace from outside are continuing with increasing intensity. The aim of these operations sanctioned by the present Kiev administration is to wreck the elections for Ukrainian president by provoking a conflict between Ukraine and the Republic of Crimea, and [word indistinct] the elimination of statehood and the executive authority structures in the hope that we will lose our nerve as a result of these provocations. We will respond, as Leonid Makarovich [Kravchuk] himself said, in a fitting way to your stupidity. [end recording]
